The paper discusses the theory of competitive on-line learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that deals with algorithms that learn from a stream of data. The paper also discusses different kinds of prediction, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper touches on decision-making, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS) and social informatics (cs.SI).
